{
  "text": "Immature female rats were injected s.c. with 10-15 IU of equine chorionic gonadotropin (eCG; Calbiochem, La Jolla, CA) between 0900 and 1000 h on Day 24-25 of age in order to enhance multiple ovarian follicular development. The animals were killed 48-50 h later by cervical dislocation. COCs were collected by puncturing the large follicles with a 25-gauge needle under a stereomicroscope. Oocytes were denuded of their cumulus cells by vortex-agitation for a few minutes in culture medium as described before [CITATION_1] . Groups of a maximum of 75 COCs were cultured in organ culture dishes (Falcon, Cockeysville, MD) for 30 min to 2 h. After all treatments, the oocytes were flash frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at \u03ea80\u040aC.",
